column5: One of the local guys was out on Sunday on the closest fishable water to my house.  	It's less than a mile to his spot from my front door.
He needs a snowdog for all that gear.  Right Terry ? LOL Thanks for the pump up for ice fishing Dave.
Luckily there's only an inch of snow or dragging that thing would kill a fella!!!! Should be sled safe by the weekend.

great video, I haven't been ice fishing since I was a kid. Even then the only thing I caught was herring and a cold lol. Do the pike and walleye fight different when Ice fishing compared to summer fishing?
